We all struggle with something, right???!! (Something or somethingS I should say).
Today on this Monday, I want to encourage us to look into HOW we can work on our struggles.  How can we be less anxious…more gracious…etc.
I am reminded that I need to work on some struggles and really live out what Jesus has asked of me. We can learn and grow in knowledge, but what good is this if we don’t take ACTION to what we learn?
Practice the truths you have learned, not just to affirm the truth. Let’s live differently my Christian family!! 
Let’s live for JOY in the Lord 💟 
*Read Phillipians  4:1-9  for some commands to help* XO -D-

Do you have a strong willed child…that maybe you but heads with?? I got me one of those 🤣🫶🏻💜 Oh my rowdy Riley 💜 The older you get, the more I am realizing you are so much like ME 🫣😬 and maybe, “just maybe” that’s why we but heads 🙀🤣😘 
I’m reminded so often about God’s Grace and how I don’t deserve His grace..BUT He loves me so much that he pours out never ending grace to me and its a free gift that i could never earn… 
i am reminded that i TOO must offer grace upon grace, even when it’s hard, even when I don’t want to! God never stops giving me grace…so i TOO Must offer grace upon grace. 

I think (we as parents) are the ones we feel are to ‘do the teaching’ to our children…but guys! Dont miss what your little one may be TEACHING YOU!! Or what GOD IS TEACHING YOU!
God is always working and those bickering moments with your ‘stubborn like child that’s just like you’ … can be a learning moment for you too!!! 
💜i do believe you are making me a better person my Riley Paige. I love you SO much my rowdy one!!! and I love how beautifully and wonderfully you were made. You will do big things in this world my little love! And I’m so proud and thankful that God gave me YOU! 🤗😘 #rileypaige #givegrace #itsabuzzworld

🌷Spring days are coming and the weather after school has been so nice 🌞 Our little 🐶Beaux Beaux is doing a bit better too ❤️He has started to eat a bit, get up without assistance and his eye flutter has stopped. He still has a bit of drooping and can’t walk too well BUT we have seen improvement and that has made us so happy. What a scary scary thing to go through this past weekend. 
What’s hard is that, as a Mom to 6 girls…when faced with a family challenge, it’s not just my own emotions I have to experience and go through…it’s also being able to be a loving support for my 6 girls feelings and emotions. Talk about hard! 😢 
These days it’s getting harder and harder to allow myself to “feel” feelings. I’m a push through it, fix it and move on kind of personality. But to have some daughters who are the opposite of me and need to express their emotions …and cry…talk about a challenge for this mama!! But isn’t that beautiful? 
God still shows me everyday that I have room to GROM MYSELF! And that I am not only a parent who needs to teach her children…but I too am a child, a child of God 💜 
And have so much learning to still do! #childofgod #momlife #girlmom #itsabuzzworld

Wow! Just wow! 🥲 Im a MOM! A Mommy. A Mama! 🥰 There really is no greater gift I could ever have received/receive. 
I prayed for years to be a Mom and when trials came and that wasn’t (at the time) Gods timing, it was so hard. But God knew (always) what He was doing for My good and little did I know one day I would be a Momto SIX. (It’s still so shocking to me that I have so many kids 🤣).
As I look back on my life story…God was (and is) present in every moment. I have walked the struggles of infertility before becoming a mommy to Blayke, then walked through a struggle of ‘how do I ask God for more (kids) when He had already blessed me with what I prayed for’ , to then… never imagining what God had in-store for me next …to become a Mom to all girl Quintuplets 😳, AND then live a life of complete surrender to Him as I walked through the NICU life with 5 babies. Y’all! These girls of mine are more than my children, they are MY Gospel Story. They brought me to Jesus and continuously remind me daily how important God is in my daily life. 
If you want to know HOW I do this life??? The answer is JESUS! ⭐️
I do not deserve this life of mine, but God sees something that I don’t. I lean to Him EVERY SINGLE DAY to bring me patience, peace, strength, grace and so much more. 
I am here today, continuing to try and survive as a Wife, Mom, sister, friend, leader…and guess what!?! I fail daily!! But Gods grace is enough and his mercies never end!
🌼 Happy Mothers Day to all my Mamas 🌼
——Words of encouragement——
 “the steadfast love of the Lord never ceases; his mercies never come to an end; they are new every morning; great is your faithfulness” (Lamentations 3:22-23) AMEN!!😘

As a mom of quintuplets, you can imagine how hard it is to stay on top of everyone’s each individual learning achievements. 
I’m sure you could imagine how long it would take for me to do one on one with each quint every day, and though it is extremely important… I just physically can’t do this all on my own. 

This Summer we started using AT&T The Achievery, a safe and also ⭐️FREE⭐️ learning platform.  This platform helps me, as a mom to quintuplets, keep them each engaged over the summer so they don’t regress academically. The quints don’t know they are “learning” because this platform keeps them intrigued, as it combines learning and entertainment from popular movies and shows. Each of our girls is strong & weak in different academic areas and The Achievery allows each quint to work on the level at which they are.

If you’re a Mom like me with a bunch of little ones, I highly recommend signing up for The Achievery at www.theachievery.com (remember, it’s FREE)! It really helps me to manage each of the quints learning time altogether. @attimpact

My Quintuplet, Baby D, Riley Paige 💜 You, my darling, are a baby in my pregnancy that I will never forget. You were a constant pain (like physical pain) in my side 🤰🤪 constantly kicking, pushing, punching all the things you could to try to make room, but there was never any room to be found… especially when there are five babies in that one belly. You sat on top of Olivia in the womb and I’m pretty sure this is why you and Olivia have that ‘rivalry sister love’ for each other…🤣 she felt the brunt of all these kicks and punches too.  Riley Paige, you are one true blessing to this world and into MY life.  Your life story, at being only 3 days old, allowed me to see God, understand God and actually FEEL God in a way I never had before. You have taught me so much… so much! patience & grace I didn’t know I could ever have.  You are so headstrong, determined and so incredibly smart. You aren’t afraid of much, know what you want, and you strive for excellence. You are witty just like your daddy and a leader just like your mommy! You love snacks more than anything in life, and your love for creatures & animals is so thrilling to watch. I can not wait to see the BIG things you conquer in this world Riley Paige! Mommy will always be here to cheer you on!!! You amaze me every day and I’m so thankful that God gave me you.
